          section#conclusion.mb-5
            h2.h4.mb-3 Final thoughts and resources
            
            p.mb-3
              | Moving to my own domain turned out to be one of the better decisions I've made for my online presence.
              | The process was more straightforward than I initially thought, especially with tools like Cloudflare handling the technical details.
            
            p.mb-3
              | The key takeaway is that with proper planning and the right tools, you can migrate domains without losing your SEO value.
              | In my case, the new domain actually ended up performing better than the old subdomain after everything settled.
            
            h3.h6.mb-3 Key success factors
            
            ul.mb-4
              li.mb-2
                strong Thorough planning:
                |  Taking time to audit and prepare made the actual migration much smoother
              li.mb-2
                strong Proper redirects:
                |  301 redirects are absolutely critical for preserving SEO value
              li.mb-2
                strong Patient monitoring:
                |  Don't panic at temporary fluctuations - they're normal
              li
                strong Clear communication:
                |  Keeping your audience informed helps maintain trust and traffic
            
